## Pinned Repository Blurb (for your GitHub profile)

**The Lift Survival Function — Jump Theorem** · [Live](https://wessengetachew.github.io/Jump/)

The function C(x) is an Euler product recording the fraction of coprime residues that survive the modular lift from ring M to M+1. Its log-derivative D(x) is smooth everywhere except at the primes, where it jumps by exactly 1/(p(p−1)). Given the jump size, the prime is recovered by a quadratic formula that always returns an integer — because the discriminant (2p−1)² is always a perfect square. The golden ratio φ is the unique irrational boundary where this integer property breaks down.

Live interactive file: no dependencies, no build step.

Part of a broader project: [wessengetachew.github.io/Sierpi-ski/](https://wessengetachew.github.io/Sierpi-ski/)

